    {
      "question": "In the given figure, $PA$ and $PB$ are two tangents to a circle with centre $O$ from an external point $P$. If $\\angle APB = 80^\\circ$, then find the value of $\\angle OAB$.",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "In the quadrilateral $OAPB$, the sum of angles is $360^\\circ$. The angles at the points of contact $A$ and $B$ are $90^\\circ$ each because the radius is perpendicular to the tangent.",
          "Calculate $\\angle AOB = 180^\\circ - \\angle APB = 180^\\circ - 80^\\circ = 100^\\circ$.",
          "In $\\triangle OAB$, $OA = OB$ (radii of the same circle), which implies it is an isosceles triangle.",
          "Therefore, $\\angle OAB = \\angle OBA = (180^\\circ - 100^\\circ) / 2 = 80^\\circ / 2 = 40^\\circ$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$\\angle OAP = \\angle OBP = 90^\\circ \\\\ \\angle AOB + \\angle APB = 180^\\circ \\\\ \\angle AOB = 180^\\circ - 80^\\circ = 100^\\circ \\\\ \\text{In } \\triangle OAB, OA = OB \\Rightarrow \\angle OAB = \\angle OBA \\\\ \\angle OAB + \\angle OBA + \\angle AOB = 180^\\circ \\\\ 2 \\angle OAB = 180^\\circ - 100^\\circ \\\\ \\angle OAB = 40^\\circ$"
      },
